Equifax Immigration Case Management Chrome E-File extension
Easily feed form data from the ICM application to government e-file systems!

The Equifax E-File solution allows users to seamlessly feed data completed within the ICM system over to government e-file systems. 

Currently built to support the ETA-9141, DS-160, ETA-9035, H-1B Registration and soon to be released ETA-9089, with plans to add more form options in the future.

The DS-160 currently supports the following visa types: H, K1, K2, K3, K4, L1, L2, P, and E Visa. 

Easy to navigate, the extension features a clean design and simple controls to feed data into new or existing cases into government e-file sites.

No restrictions! Use of this extension is available to all Equifax ICM users. No add-ons required. As the extension populates information, specialized pop-ups prompting for errors or specific data input will appear. 

Disclaimer:
Use of this extension requires an Equifax ICM user account as well as credentials necessary to access certain government e-file systems. 

The Equifax E-File extension is designed for the sole purpose of populating information into forms for electronic submission. Equifax highly recommends that you carefully review all information populated before submitting to ensure accuracy.

Please note that Equifax cannot guarantee application acceptance due to extenuating circumstances, such as website technical issues or changes made by the government. You are responsible for verifying the status and confirming receipt of the application by the government agency once submitted. By continuing, you acknowledge and agree to the above.
